snippet.title: LIVE: Emergency Action Messages Alert! Ham Radio Monitoring WW3 Tensions & IRAN Crisis on Icom
snippet.description:
Join us live from our ham radio shack in Lower New York as we fire up the Icom IC-7300 to scan and attempt to understand real-time Emergency Action Messages (EAMs) amid escalating global hotspots. With U.S.-Iran tensions boiling over—UN Security Council warnings, alleged U.S. boat strikes on drug networks, and Maduro's military buildup—we're tuning into potential WW3 signals. Expect live frequency sweeps on HF bands, signal analysis, and updates on Guyana border disputes, Russian alliances, and broader Middle East ripple effects. Whether you're a fellow radio enthusiast or prepping for uncertainty, this is your front-row seat to the airwaves. QSL if you copy!

Drop your callsign in chat, share your scans, and let's monitor together. Gear: Icom IC-7300, dipole antenna optimized for 3-30 MHz. Stay tuned—signals don't wait!

snippet.title: DATOS PARA EJERCICIO DE COMUNICACIÓN HF ¿QUIERES PARTICIPAR?
snippet.description:
Ejercicio de Comunicaciones HF sin Soporte | Radioafición en el Campo 🌲

En este video te llevo conmigo a un ejercicio práctico de comunicaciones en HF sin ningún tipo de soporte, saliendo al campo con equipo básico y esencial para comprobar hasta dónde podemos llegar únicamente con conocimientos, planificación y radio 📡.

Te explicaré paso a paso:
🔹 En qué consiste un ejercicio de comunicaciones HF sin soporte
🔹 Qué equipo mínimo utilizo (radio, antena y alimentación)
🔹 Cómo preparo la estación portátil en el campo
🔹 Resultados reales: contactos con estaciones de todo el país
🔹 Consejos y lecciones aprendidas para radioaficionados que quieran iniciarse en este tipo de actividades

Este tipo de ejercicios son ideales para entrenamiento, emergencias, SOTA, POTA o simplemente disfrutar de la radioafición al aire libre, demostrando que no se necesita una gran infraestructura para lograr excelentes comunicaciones.

👉 Si te gusta la radio HF, la operación portátil y los desafíos reales, este video es para ti.

🔔 Suscríbete, dale 👍 al video y deja en los comentarios tu experiencia operando HF en portátil.

snippet.title: How To Get A Business License In SC?
snippet.description:
How To Get A Business License In SC?

Obtaining a business license in South Carolina is a local process, as no single statewide general license exists. Your primary step is to identify the specific city or county where your business operates, as each jurisdiction has unique requirements, application forms, and fee structures. For businesses within city limits, contact that city's business license department. If operating in an unincorporated area, reach out to the county's administration or permitting office. ✅단순히 "뚜뚜-띡" 소리로만 생각했던 모스 부호가 사실은 일반적인 타이핑 속도보다 빠를 수 있다는 사실, 알고 계셨나요?

💡 모스 부호 상식 사전
✅단점(.)과 장점(-): 모스 부호의 기본 단위입니다. 장점 하나는 단점 세 개의 길이를 가집니다.
분당 단어 수(WPM): 모스 부호 속도를 측정하는 단위로, 숙련된 운영자들은 보통 20~40 WPM(약 분당 100~200자) 이상의 속도로 소통합니다.
✅파리(PARIS) 기준: 모스 부호 속도를 잴 때 기준이 되는 단어입니다. 'PARIS'라는 단어를 전송하는 데 걸리는 시간을 기준으로 속도를 계산하죠.
📜 비하인드 스토리 모스 부호는 단순히 글자를 전송하는 것을 넘어, 운영자마다 고유의 '필체(Fist)'가 있다고 합니다. 숙련자들은 상대방의 두드리는 리듬만 듣고도 "아, 이건 누구구나!"라고 바로 알아차릴 수 있죠. 마치 우리가 목소리만 듣고 친구를 알아보는 것과 같습니다.

🔔 구독과 좋아요, 알림 설정 부탁드립니다!

snippet.title: Which Ham Radio Should I Buy? Keland Draney (KM7G) | Idaho ERC Net, January 7, 2026
snippet.description:
Are you new to ham radio and feeling overwhelmed by the options? You’re not alone! In this on-air training session from the Idaho ERC Net, Keland Draney (KM7G) breaks down everything a beginner needs to know to choose their first radio.

From affordable handhelds (HTs) to powerful mobile rigs and base stations, we cover the pros and cons of popular models, the importance of antenna choice, and how power output affects your range. Whether you're interested in local emergency communications or reaching across the globe, this guide will help you get started on the right foot.

Radio Recommendations for Beginners

1. Entry-Level Handhelds (HTs)
Best for: Beginners on a budget and local repeater use.
● BaoFeng UV-5R Series: Extremely affordable, dual-band (2m/70cm), and a great low-risk entry point.
● Yaesu FT-60R: A legendary, rugged choice known for its superior build quality and "front-end" performance in high-interference areas.
● Yaesu FT-70DR: A solid entry point into digital modes (C4FM/System Fusion) alongside standard analog FM.

2. Mobile & Base Stations (VHF/UHF)
Best for: Better range from a vehicle or home setup.
● Dual-Band Mobile Rigs: Look for 10-50 watt units from reputable brands like Yaesu, Icom, or Kenwood. These provide significantly more "punch" than a handheld.

3. High-Frequency (HF) & Multi-Band Rigs
Best for: Long-distance (DX) communication and advanced users.
● Icom IC-7300: A highly popular, user-friendly HF base station with a beautiful color touchscreen and waterfall display.
● Yaesu FT-991A: An "all-in-one" powerhouse covering HF, VHF, and UHF bands in all modes.
● Yaesu FT-891: A compact, 100-watt HF rig perfect for mobile or portable (SOTA/POTA) operations.

Pro-Tips from the Net:
● Upgrade Your Antenna: A handheld radio is only as good as its antenna. Consider a Signal Stick (made by Signal Stuff) for your HT or a magnetic mount antenna for your vehicle.
● Ask an Elmer: Connect with local experienced hams (Elmers) to see what equipment is most effective in your specific terrain.
● Check the Modes: Before buying, find out if your local area primarily uses Analog, DMR, D-Star, or Fusion.

Where to buy? 
● GigaParts: https://gigaparts.com
● Ham Radio Outlet: https://www.hamradio.com/
● DX Engineering: https://www.dxengineering.com/
